🔹 Code Line:-
IncrementalObjectIterator identities = new IncrementalObjectIterator(context, Identity.class, qo);
🧠 Ye karta kya hai?
👉 Ye DB se data ko ek-ek karke (incrementally) fetch karta hai
👉 Matlab:-
Bulk me nahi, thoda-thoda load karta hai (memory safe)

🔥 Breakdown (हर चीज समझ):-
🔸 1. IncrementalObjectIterator
👉 Special iterator hai SailPoint ka
👉 Use hota hai:-
Large data handle karne ke liye
Memory crash se bachne ke liye.

⚡ Ye kaise kaam karta hai?
DB me 1 lakh identities hai
        ↓
Iterator ek baar me 100-100 load karega
        ↓
Loop me process hoga
        ↓
Memory safe 👍

import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import sailpoint.object.QueryOptions;
import sailpoint.object.Filter;
import sailpoint.tools.IncrementalObjectIterator;

QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("inactive", false));

IncrementalObjectIterator identities =
    new IncrementalObjectIterator(context, Identity.class, qo);

int count = 0;

while (identities.hasNext()) {
    Identity id = (Identity) identities.next();

    count++;
    log.info("Identity Name: " + id.getName());
}

log.info("Total Count: " + count);
🔥 Output
Identity Name: raj
Identity Name: amit
Identity Name: neha
Total Count: 3